<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-26-0056 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Working Group continued its former activities of the 1971 to 1982period. The following main tasks were established: Further developmentof conventional winning methods and equipment in terms of performance,daily utilisation factor, applicability in difficult mining conditions,and longer service life; development of drum shearers for seams up to1 m thick, in which coal ploughs would be economically inefficient; automation,as far as possible, of face equipment such as winning machines and poweredsupports; development of equipment, especially roadheaders, for efficientand low-cost rise heading.</TEXT></DOC>